This paper is primarily focused on the impact of importance weighting in deep learning, which is a key ingredient in many machine learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these fields heavily rely on deep learning. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of regularization techniques such as L2 regularization and batch normalization, which are commonly used in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the effect of importance weighting on datasets, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
